{{Quote|Accompanying Koon on aerial patrol of Cato Neimoidia's bridge cities, Jag (CT-55/11-9009) and CT-57/11-9048 received Order 66 and fired several shots from the wing cannons of the ARC-170 starfighters belonging to the 127th.|[[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Marcellin Wessel]], in a report to [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]|<ref name="Insider87" />}}
The '''127th Gunship Wing''' was a unit in the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

==History==
{{Quote|Execute Order 66."<br />"It will be done, my Lord.|Palpatine, to Jai'galaar|<ref name="Episode 3">{{Film|III}}</ref>}}
One of the first divisions commissioned, the 127th first saw action at the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|Battle of Geonosis]] and participated throughout the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. It was led by [[Clone Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Jai'galaar (clone)|Jai'galaar]] during the Battle of Geonosis. Commander Jai'galaar was later demoted to [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] for his actions during the disastrous [[Retreat at Katraasii]]. However, [[Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Plo Koon/Legends|Plo Koon]] nominated Captain Jag as a test [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] for the new [[Aggressive ReConnaissance-170 starfighter/Legends|Aggressive ReConnaissance-170 starfighter]].<ref name="Insider84" />

During the [[Battle of Cato Neimoidia/Legends|Battle of Cato Neimoidia]], the 127th was equipped with ARC-170 starfighters. After execution of [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], Captain Jag and [[CT-57/11-9048]] eliminated [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] Plo Koon.<ref name="Insider87" />

